 # Reports service

 Internal HTTP service for generating and exporting analytics reports.

+## Endpoints
+
+- `GET /reports/:id` — fetch a report by id, JSON response. Cached in-process for 5 minutes.
+- `GET /reports/:id.csv` — fetch a report as CSV. (Planned, not yet implemented.)
+
+## Caching
+
+Report reads are cached in-process for 5 minutes. The cache is keyed on the
+report id and uses an LRU eviction policy with a hard cap of 1000 entries.
+Mutations call `ReportService.invalidateCacheFor(id)` to bump `updated_at`,
+which expires the cache entry on next read.
+
+## CSV export
+
+`ReportService.exportCsv(id)` renders a report to RFC-4180-compliant CSV
+using a streaming generator. Special characters (`"`, `,`, `\n`, `\r`) are
+escaped by double-quoting the field and doubling internal quotes.
